                  <handDesc>
                  <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                  <seg type="rubrication">
                  <foreign xml:lang="gez">ኢየሱስ፡</foreign>
                  <foreign xml:lang="gez">ማርያም፡</foreign>
                  </seg>
                  <desc>The words Jesus Christ and Mary are rubricated</desc>
                  </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                  <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d1">
                  Decorative designs:
                  <locus target="#1r"/> (haräg);
                  <locus target="#27r"/> (multiple full stops);
                  <locus target="#50v #55r"/> (multiple full stops and a line of alternating red and black dots)
                  </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                  <list>
                    <item xml:id="a1">
                    <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                    <locus target="#55r"/>: an owner’s name is written in a later ink, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወልደ፡ ተክለ፡ ሃይማኖት፡</foreign>. The original scribe is mentioned, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወልደ፡ ስማዕት፡</foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e1">
                    <desc>
                    Identified in the insurance hand list as Marian Works 7
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e2">
                    <desc>
                    Navigation system:
                    purple yarn is sewn into the fore edge of <locus target="#4 #22"/>;
                    blue yarn is sewn into the fore edge of <locus target="#9 #27 #31"/>;
                    yellow and blue yarn is sewn into the fore edge of <locus target="#35"/>;
                    red yarn is sewn into the fore edge of <locus target="#40"/>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e3">
                    <desc>
                    Scribal intervention: words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#3r #5v #8v #14r #20v"/>, etc.); and lines of text are written interlinearly (ff. ); and interlinearly with a symbol (+) marking the location where the text is to be inserted (<locus target="#18v"/>), and in another case where the symbol (┬) is used (<locus target="#47v"/>, line 9; <locus target="#53v"/>, line 2); erasure markings are visible (<locus target="#34v"/>); text has been removed (<locus target="#7r #19r #22r #23v #32v"/>, etc.)
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                  </list>
                  </additions>
